he page opens into the compositional field that Mallarmé, Ponge, and others conceived it to be, words constellate around bolded through-lines to offer multiple, interwoven meanings, interacting with each other and the reader, who moves freely among them, to make poems that are spatial, nonlinear, and different with each reading. And, adding yet another dimension to the collection, many of the poems have facing-page French versions.“Landscape-oriented” in every sense, I entered without words is an ambitious, innovative, and striking collection by a major poet.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  aAcid-free paper.  aAll rights reserved.  aAncient Greece.  aBibliography.  aClassical Athens.  aClothing.  aDavid Hinton.  aDavid Lehman.  aDora Maar.  aFirmament.  aFlesh.  aFreedom of speech.  aHarvard Review.  aHeat.  aIntellectual property.  aJean Valentine.  aLeather.  aLiang Qichao.  aLibrary of Congress.  aMy Child.  aNewspaper.  aPoet.  aPoetry.  aPrinceton University Press.  aPrinting.  aPublication.  aRalph Angel.  aScrap.  aShakespeare's plays.  aShorthand.  aStock exchange.  aThucydides.  aTiananmen Square.  aVirgil.  aWashing.  aWealth.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074973140uhttps://doi.org/1